reviewText:
This review is for this shirt in XL worn by a 6' 5" 200lbs male.

// FEEL & WEIGHT
The first thing i noticed was how lightweight the shirt was, maybe half the weight of a regular tee shirt? Feels silk smooth in hand and when worn it's like it's not even there.

// FIT
When I put this shirt on the sleeves always become twisted around my arm and I have to spend a minute getting them straight. This is because the arms are a little bit snug in the forearms, more so than the rest of the shirt. I don't have Popeye forearms, actually they are quite slender. If you have large arms, especially forearms, this shirt might bug you (unless you enjoy really tight sleeves.)

The length of the sleeves are great for me. Again, 6' 5" wearing an XL, and the sleeves got an inch or so beyond my wrist. Really great coverage.

// MATERIAL
I first thought 'I'm going to be hot' when I saw it is 84% polyester, 16% spandex. But it's not! It's actually cooler than cotton. Really surprised by that. A nice breeze going by makes the fabric really cool as it wicks the moisture away and cools the fabric.

// GREAT FOR
This shirt would be great for people with full arm sleeve tattoos as the sleeve goes down to your hand and blocks the sun with UPF 50+ sunblock level. Great way to protect your work from getting wrecked by the sun.

Also great for activities where you need your shirt to stay close to your body. While I am wearing the shirt, it hangs very much in the same way ti does in the pictures of the model. A little bit of slack in the torso, but not much.

I received a free sample of this product to evaluate and provide an unbiased review.
